Enabling Travis-CI service.
Simple test for nominal pull_request and ping cases.
Factor out the Kwalitee object for github events.
Giving back the stacktrace in case of exception.
Using nose with coverage for tests.

Refactoring of check_messages (with tests).

* check_messages is no longer responsible to talk to GitHub anymore.

* check_message checks one message at the time (hence no trailing s).

* _check_bullets accepts only "*" as a bullet character.

* _check_bullets doesn't allow signatures between/before some bullet points.

* 100% coverage tested.
Better error messages and true 100% coverage.
Putting the access_token authorization back in.
Better documentation and usage of the assertions.
Testing GET /status/sha1 and clean up post-test.

Removing useless main function

* gunicorn or paster are great alternatives to run your development
  server.
Testing the homepage.

Python 2.6 is not supported anymore.

* unittest.TestCase.assertIn and assertRegexpMatches were introduced in
  Python 2.7. TestCase could be monkeypatched in the future to work
  around this.
Ignore pull requests with title "WIP"
Test coverage addition
Fix missing filename in test
README updates
travis configuration improvements
Python 3.3 compatibility fixes
Fix test assertRegex
README: coverage with nosetests
pragma: no cover for unused lines

Simplify wip test.

* No records are kept for it (status.txt)

* wip should not be part of a word, e.g. "wipe"

Asynchronous refactoring using RQ.

* when a new event arises, it's sent to a background worker and the PR
  state is set to pending.

Deployment section in the README

* How to setup the worker in a production environment
PEP8 checks on the whole files.

PEP8 errors into the review view.

* The commit messages error displayed into the commit itself and the file
  related comments are put into the review view (on line 1)
Fix multiline bullet point seen as signatures.
PyFlakes checks on the whole files.
Refactoring.
Options in config for commits, pep8, flakes, wip.
Fix ignored PEP8_IGNORE option.
Read PEP8 ignore from config
Comment on line with first problem

Using pyHamcrest for testing (Python 2.6 support)

* Enabling Travis testing for 2.6, 2.7, 3.3
* Adding the corresponding classifiers in setup.py

Testing the license in python files.

* empty files are ignored (use case: `__init__.py`)
* new set of codes starting with "I"
* fuzzy test that it looks like the GNU GPLv2 (or GNU GPLv3)
Testing the license in Jinja files.
Fix work-in-progress check
Refactoring the messages error codes.

Need more reviewers only appears as a label change.

* in_work if "WIP" is in the title
* in_review if a "needs more reviewers" error is found
* in_integration if no "needs more reviewers" errors exist
Enabling worker logging on Python 2.6.
If an error is found, the label is in_review.

Fix labels and add better tests.

cli: check authors

* NEW Adds new checking option `kwalitee check authors` to check whether
  the source code committers are also well listed in the AUTHORS or
  THANKS files. The list of author files is customisable via `authors`
  directive in `.kwalitee.yml`. The list of author names to exclude from
  checking (e.g. known second email addresses) is customisable via
  `exclude_author_names` directive in `.kwalitee.yml`.
